Interface EETClient


  • public interface EETClient
    EET client implementation, handling computation of security codes, signing of requests, validation of responses.

    • Method Detail

      • prepareFirstRequest

        TrzbaType prepareFirstRequest(TrzbaDataType receiptData,
                              CommunicationMode mode)
                       throws DataSigningException
        Prepare request for first submit to EET Service.
        Parameters:
        receiptData - Receipt data like price, VAT or Tax ID.
        mode - test or real communication (will be encoded in header
        Returns:
        complete request, including computed security codes, added random message UUID, current date.
        Throws:
        DataSigningException - if problem with signing occurs. Should be related to client key in that case

      • prepareRepeatedRequest

        TrzbaType prepareRepeatedRequest(TrzbaType request)
                          throws DataSigningException
        Prepare request for second or every other submit to EET service.
        Parameters:
        request - the original request, which has been already constructed and sent to EET servers.
        Returns:
        Updated request, re-generated message UUID, send date, set first-submission flag to false, recomputed security codes if they change meanwhile (new client certificate used for this submission)
        Throws:
        DataSigningException - if problem with signing occurs. Should be related to client key in that case

      • sendSync

        SubmitResult sendSync(TrzbaType request,
                      EndpointType endpointType)
               throws CommunicationException
        Submit synchronously a receipt to EET servers.
        Parameters:
        request - prepared by calling one of prepareFirstRequest(TrzbaDataType, CommunicationMode) or prepareRepeatedRequest(TrzbaType) method.
        endpointType - real or test endpoint
        Returns:
        result provided by EET servers.
        Throws:
        CommunicationException - if something fails. It may be timeout, not accessible servers, invalid message, invalid signature of response.

      • sendAsync

        Future<?> sendAsync(TrzbaType request,
                    EndpointType endpointType,
                    ResponseCallback handler)
        Submit asynchronously a receipt to EET servers.
        Parameters:
        request - prepared by calling one of prepareFirstRequest(TrzbaDataType, CommunicationMode) or prepareRepeatedRequest(TrzbaType) method.
        endpointType - real or test endpoint
        handler - callback for response or failure of the call
        Returns:
        result future you can wait on

      • submitReceipt

        @Deprecated
SubmitResult submitReceipt(TrzbaDataType receipt,
                                       CommunicationMode mode,
                                       EndpointType endpointType,
                                       SubmissionType submissionType)
                                throws DataSigningException,
                                       CommunicationException
        Deprecated. 
        Central method of EET. Send the receipt data to selected endpoint, select if it's first or repeated submission and if the communication is test only or real. This method is DEPRECATED. Prepare data using prepareFirstRequest first, then send them using one of send* methods.
        Parameters:
        receipt - Receipt data - price, date, tax numbers, ...
        mode - real or test submission
        endpointType - playground or real endpoint
        submissionType - first or repeated submission
        Returns:
        EET response with added request needed to access security codes and other data in case of failed submission
        Throws:
        DataSigningException - Failed to compute PKP or BKP
        CommunicationException - Failed to send or receive data from EET endpoint
